Finance Manager
Responsibilities
A rapidly growing multinational luxury fashion retail company is looking for a Finance Manager in Jakarta to lead a team of individuals in providing financial and operational support. Responsibilities:Leading Finance team in preparation of statutory accounts and financial reportsReview and prepare financial statement and management reportsCo-ordinate with external and internal audit activitiesPrepare budget, forecast and variance analysis including recommendation for improvementParticipate in any special accounting related projectsAny other duties as may assigned from time to time Responsible for controllership and credit control/collectionOversee corporate tax planning and compliance Requirements:Previous experience in financial reporting and budgetingRetail/wholesale background is an added advantageDegree qualified professional accountant7 to 8 years of experience in Finance function from an MNCStrong team player and good leadership skillAble to work in a fast pace environmentFluent EnglishHighly motivated individual with initiative
Requirements
Company Overview
Robert Walters Jakarta was established in 2012 and due to continual expansion is seeking highly entrepreneurial, motivated recruitment consultants to grow the business. Jakarta is one of the worlds largest cities, is internationalising rapidly, with a corresponding increase in demand for an international standard of recruitment services. Robert Walters is one of the world's leading global specialist recruitment and recruitment outsourcing businesses. The Group specialises in permanent and contract recruitment across all industry sectors, and count FORTUNE 500 companies, investment banks and multinational blue-chip commercial organisations as clients. Operating at all levels of seniority, Jakarta - Indonesia office manages the careers of the best professionals in the following disciplines: commerce finance, banking & financial services, engineering, human resources, legal, information technology, sales & marketing, supply chain, procurement & logistics, and support and administration fields.
